{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using Swift’s structured concurrency in SwiftUI it is good practice to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tie the tasks to the relevant view’s lifetime in order to support task"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cancellation should the view be dismissed.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Info","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Usually a task might not take all that long that we would even care for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cancellation. But imagine downloading some large amounts of data from a remote"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"server which – depending on the network connection – could take a consiterable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"amount of time. When the user decides to dismiss the view it might be good to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"also cancel the task to not keep doing no longer necessary work."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Of course this does not guarantee that the child tasks will instantly stop but rather","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"they will be informed via ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task.isCancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that they’ve been cancelled. If or how","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"they handle cancellation is entirely up to the implementation of the child task.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The Problem","anchor":"The-Problem"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This can already be achieved by using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task(id:priority:_:)"},{"text":" view modifier.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However this requires additional housekeeping for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a primitive example where we just want to trigger some task we might use a "},{"code":"Bool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@State var triggerTask: Bool = false","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        triggerTask = true","    }","    .task(id: triggerTask) {","        guard triggerTask else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation()","        triggerTask = false","    }","}"]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We need to check that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" is indeed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":", and otherwise return.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"We also need to reset "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end of execution. Otherwise another"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tap wouldn’t trigger the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task(id:priority:_:)"},{"text":" again.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first step is crucial becuase we would trigger the task again from in itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when we reset ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"triggerTask"},{"type":"text","text":" at the end."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This makes even more sense in a more complicated example where we have a list of views","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"where we would like to do something based on some identifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@State var triggerTaskId: Int?","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            triggerTaskId = index","        }","    }","    .task(id: triggerTaskId) {","        guard let triggerTaskId else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation(for: triggerTaskId)","        triggerTaskId = nil","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this case we have an optional integer and we set it to the index of the button"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the list once pressed. We need to unwrap the optional value and reset it to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" afterwards.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This approach, while it really works well, comes with a lot of overhead directly in our view."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Also we have to call the state value directly from within our task which might be cumbersome when we"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hold the state in a view model.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The Solution","anchor":"The-Solution"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To make things simpler on the caller’s side let’s wrap all of this functionality inside","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a simple type ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@State var trigger = TaskTrigger<Int>()","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            trigger.trigger(value: index)","        }","    }","    .task($trigger) { index in","        await someAsyncOperation(for: index)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We declare a new state variable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" and initialize the "},{"code":"TaskTrigger","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of type "},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In our button we call the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method on our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"text":" and pass in our value.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We attach a new variant of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view modifier to our view and bind it to our ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The body will only execute when the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" was triggered. The value we passed into the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method earlier gets passed into the closure as an argument."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All cancellation related handling, sanity checking, as well as resetting the state is handled"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically behind the scenes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"aside","name":"Info","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You might wonder why there’s an optional parameter ","type":"text"},{"code":"id","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","isActive":true},{"text":" method.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"By default this will create a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"text":" whenever the method is called. This means we can tap the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"same button multiple times and prior operations will get cancelled if they are still running.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In case you don’t want that to happen explicitly set the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":" parameter and it won’t cancel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"prior operations since both the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":" are still the same.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For triggers that don’t need to attach a value, we can simply use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger"},{"type":"text","text":" (which is a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"typealias for "},{"code":"TaskTrigger<Bool>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var trigger = PlainTaskTrigger()","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        trigger.trigger()","    }","    .task($trigger) {","        await someAsyncOperation()","    }","}"]}]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Triggers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/SwiftUI"],"title":"Extended Modules"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tasktrigger"]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"TaskTrigger"}],"role":"collection","title":"TaskTrigger","roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"TaskTrigger","symbolKind":"module"},"references":{"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/SwiftUI":{"title":"SwiftUI","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/swiftui","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/SwiftUI","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"TaskTrigger","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TaskTrigger","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TaskTrigger","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"TaskTrigger","abstract":[{"text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger","role":"collection"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/PlainTaskTrigger":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation."}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PlainTaskTrigger","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/plaintasktrigger","title":"PlainTaskTrigger","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PlainTaskTrigger"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger","kind":"symbol"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger/trigger(value:id:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers the tasks associated with this "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and passes along a value of type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"trigger"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"value","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:11TaskTriggerAAV5Valuexmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"id","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation4UUIDV","text":"UUID"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","title":"trigger(value:id:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","kind":"symbol"}}}